  "prompt": "What happens if you overdose on Naproxen?",
  "response": "An overdose of Naproxen can be serious and potentially life-threatening. Symptoms may include:\n\n1. Gastrointestinal effects:\n- Stomach pain\n- Nausea and vomiting\n- Bleeding or ulceration\n\n2. Cardiovascular effects:\n- Low blood pressure\n- Rapid heartbeat\n- Potential heart failure\n\n3. Neurological symptoms:\n- Drowsiness\n- Confusion\n- Seizures\n- Potential coma\n\n4. Kidney problems:\n- Reduced kidney function\n- Potential kidney failure\n\n5. Respiratory issues:\n- Breathing difficulties\n\nIf you suspect a Naproxen overdose, seek immediate medical attention. Treatment typically involves:\n- Activated charcoal\n- Supportive care\n- Monitoring of vital signs\n- Treating specific symptoms\n\nNever exceed recommended dosage, and always consult a healthcare professional about proper medication use.",
